name: getIsPotionDurationMax
desc: Get the value of the isPotionDurationMax field.

name: setPotionDurationMax
desc: Toggle the isPotionDurationMax field.

name: isNoDespawnRequired
desc: Return the persistenceRequired field (whether this entity is allowed to naturally despawn)

name: setForceGamemode
desc: Set the forceGamemode field (whether joining players will be put in their old gamemode or the default one)

name: getForceGamemode
desc: Get the forceGamemode field (whether joining players will be put in their old gamemode or the default one)

name: isNotEmpty
desc: Returns true if the given string is neither null nor empty.

name: getUniqueID
desc: Returns the UUID of this entity.

name: onBroken
desc: Called when this entity is broken. Entity parameter may be null.

name: removeItem
desc: Removes the dot representing this frame's position from the map when the item frame is broken.

name: removeListener
desc: removes the specified IInvBasic from receiving further change notices

name: addListener
desc: Add a listener that will be notified when any item in this inventory is modified.

name: getMaxHealth
desc: Returns the maximum health of the entity (what it is able to regenerate up to, what it spawned with, etc)

name: getAbsorptionAmount
desc: Returns the amount of health added by the Absorption effect.

name: getAttributeMap
desc: Returns this entity's attribute map (where all its attributes are stored)

name: dismountEntity
desc: Moves the entity to a position out of the way of its mount.

name: updateLeashedState
desc: Applies logic related to leashes, for example dragging the entity or breaking the leash.

name: clearLeashed
desc: Removes the leash from this entity

name: setLeashHolder
desc: Sets the entity to be leashed to.

name: enablePersistence
desc: Enable the Entity persistence

name: addGrowth
desc: Increases this entity's age. If the entity is an adult (if the entity's age is greater than or equal to 0) then the entity's age will be set to {@link #forcedAge}. This method does not update {@link #forcedAge}.

name: canMate
desc: Return true if the horse entity ready to mate. (no rider, not riding, tame, adult, not steril...)

name: getModifiedMovementSpeed
desc: Returns randomized movement speed

name: spawnHorseParticles
desc: "Spawns particles for the horse entity. par1 tells whether to spawn hearts. If it is false, it spawns smoke."

name: updateHorseSlots
desc: Updates the items in the saddle and armor slots of the horse's inventory.

name: getModifiedJumpStrength
desc: Returns randomized jump strength

name: getModifiedMaxHealth
desc: Returns randomized max health

name: verifySellingItem
desc: Notifies the merchant of a possible merchantrecipe being fulfilled or not. Usually, this is just a sound byte being played depending if the suggested itemstack is not null.

name: getLocationSkin
desc: Returns the ResourceLocation associated with the player's skin

name: getLocationSkin
desc: Returns true if the username has an associated skin.

name: getSectionName
desc: The name of this section type as it appears in JSON.

name: getTextWithoutFormattingCodes
desc: Returns a copy of the given string, with formatting codes stripped away.

name: isRidingHorse
desc: Checks if the player is riding a horse, used to chose the GUI to open

name: getEntityTexture
desc: Returns the location of an entity's texture. Doesn't seem to be called unless you call Render.bindEntityTexture.

name: getAttribute
desc: Get the Attribute this is an instance of

name: getModifier
desc: Returns attribute modifier, if any, by the given UUID

name: registerAttribute
desc: Registers an attribute with this AttributeMap, returns a modifiable AttributeInstance associated with this map

name: isSaved
desc: @see #isSaved

name: setSaved
desc: @see #isSaved

name: getAttributeModifiers
desc: Gets a map of item attribute modifiers, used by ItemSword to increase hit damage.

name: itemInteractionForEntity
desc: Returns true if the item can be used on the given entity, e.g. shears on sheep.

name: getRelevantEnchantmentTypes
desc: Returns the enchantment types relevant to this tab

name: setRelevantEnchantmentTypes
desc: Sets the enchantment types for populating this tab with enchanting books

name: isEnabled
desc: Actualy only call when we want to render the white square effect over the slots. Return always True, except for the armor slot of the Donkey/Mule (we can't interact with the Undead and Skeleton horses)

name: getPathSearchRange
desc: Gets the maximum distance that the path finding will search in.

name: getAttributeModifiers
desc: Gets the attribute modifiers for this ItemStack.\nWill check for an NBT tag list containing modifiers for the stack.

name: getStatsComponent
desc: Generates new StatsComponent and returns it.

name: getPlayerListComponent
desc: Generates new PlayerListComponent and returns it.

name: getCurrentMoonPhaseFactor
desc: gets the current fullness of the moon expressed as a float between 1.0 and 0.0, in steps of .25

name: getEntityWorld
desc: Get the world, if available. {@code null} is not allowed! If you are not an entity in the world, return the overworld

name: getMinecraftStartTimeMillis
desc: Returns the saved value of System#currentTimeMillis when the game started

name: formatMessage
desc: Calls String.format(translateKey(key), params)

name: translateKeyPrivate
desc: Returns the translation, or the key itself if the key could not be translated.

name: loadLocaleData
desc: Loads the locale data for the list of resources.

name: format
desc: Translates the given string and then formats it. Equivilant to String.format(translate(key), parameters).

name: replaceWith
desc: Replaces all the current instance's translations with the ones that are passed in.

name: tryTranslateKey
desc: Tries to look up a translation for the given key; spits back the key if no result was found.

name: clearCustomName
desc: Clear any custom name set for this ItemStack

name: getServerBrand
desc: Gets the brand of the currently connected server. May be null if the server hasn't yet sent brand information. Server brand information is sent over the {@code MC|Brand} plugin channel, and is used to identify modded servers in crash reports.

name: isSameTeam
desc: Same as ==

name: write
desc: Writes structure base data (id, boundingbox, {@link net.minecraft.world.gen.structure.StructureComponent#coordBaseMode coordBase} and {@link net.minecraft.world.gen.structure.StructureComponent#componentType componentType}) to new NBTTagCompound and returns it.

name: readAdditional
desc: (abstract) Helper method to read subclass data from NBT

name: sendMessage
desc: Send a chat message to the CommandSender

name: getLastOutput
desc: Returns the lastOutput.

name: setCommand
desc: Sets the command.

name: getCommand
desc: Returns the command of the command block.

name: read
desc: Reads NBT formatting and stored data into variables.

name: getSuccessCount
desc: returns the successCount int.

name: doesEntityNotTriggerPressurePlate
desc: Return whether this entity should NOT trigger a pressure plate or a tripwire.

name: validate
desc: validates a tile entity

name: hasWorld
desc: Returns true if the worldObj isn't null.

name: getWorld
desc: Returns the worldObj for this tileEntity.

name: setWorld
desc: Sets the worldObj for this tileEntity.

name: getDistanceSq
desc: Returns the square of the distance between this entity and the passed in coordinates.

name: receiveClientEvent
desc: See {@link Block#eventReceived} for more information. This must return true serverside before it is called clientside.

name: remove
desc: invalidates a tile entity

name: getProgress
desc: Get interpolated progress value (between lastProgress and progress) given the fractional time between ticks as an argument

name: clearPistonTileEntity
desc: removes a piston's tile entity (and if the piston is moving, stops it)

name: isExtending
desc: Returns true if a piston is extending

name: getSourceInventory
desc: Gets the inventory that the provided hopper will transfer items from.

name: pullItems
getInventoryAtPosition
desc: Returns the IInventory (if applicable) of the TileEntity at the specified position

name: getInventoryForHopperTransfer
desc: Returns the IInventory that this hopper is pointing into

name: setEditable
desc: Sets the sign's isEditable flag to the specified parameter.

name: addItemStack
desc: Add the given ItemStack to this Dispenser. Return the Slot the Item was placed in or -1 if no free slot is available.

name: canDropLoot
desc: Entity won't drop items or experience points if this returns false

name: setBreakDoorsAItask
desc: Sets or removes EntityAIBreakDoor task

name: explode
desc: Creates an explosion as determined by this creeper's power and explosion radius.

name: getUUID
desc: Gets a players UUID given their GameProfie

name: dropItem
desc: Creates and drops the provided item. Depending on the dropAround, it will drop teh item around the player, instead of dropping the item from where the player is pointing at. Likewise, if traceItem is true, the dropped item entity will have the thrower set as the player.

name: getGameProfile
desc: Returns the GameProfile for this player

name: getChatGUI
desc: returns a pointer to the persistant Chat GUI, containing all previous chat messages and such

name: deleteFromCursor
desc: Deletes the given number of characters from the current cursor's position, unless there is currently a selection, in which case the selection is deleted instead.

name: getVisible
desc: returns true if this textbox is visible

name: deleteWords
desc: Deletes the given number of words from the current cursor's position, unless there is currently a selection, in which case the selection is deleted instead.

name: tick
desc: Increments the cursor counter

name: getText
desc: Returns the contents of the textbox

name: setText
desc: Sets the text of the textbox, and moves the cursor to the end.

name: getEnableBackgroundDrawing
desc: Gets whether the background and outline of this text box should be drawn (true if so).

name: moveCursorBy
desc: Moves the text cursor by a specified number of characters and clears the selection

name: getNthWordFromPos
desc: Gets the starting index of the word at a distance of the specified number of words away from the given position.

name: setEnabled
desc: Sets whether this text box is enabled. Disabled text boxes cannot be typed in.

name: setEnableBackgroundDrawing
desc: Sets whether or not the background and outline of this text box should be drawn.

name: getNthWordFromCursor
desc: Gets the starting index of the word at the specified number of words away from the cursor position.

name: drawSelectionBox
desc: Draws the blue selection box.

name: setVisible
desc: Sets whether or not this textbox is visible

name: setCursorPosition
desc: Sets the current position of the cursor.

name: writeText
desc: Adds the given text after the cursor, or replaces the currently selected text if there is a selection.

name: setTextColor
desc: Sets the color to use when drawing this text box's text. A different color is used if this text box is disabled.

name: setFocused
desc: Sets focus to this gui element

name: setCursorPositionZero
desc: Moves the cursor to the very start of this text box.

name: getNthWordFromPosWS
desc: Like getNthWordFromPos (which wraps this), but adds option for skipping consecutive spaces

name: getCursorPosition
desc: returns the current position of the cursor

name: setSelectionPos
desc: Sets the position of the selection anchor (the selection anchor and the cursor position mark the edges of the selection). If the anchor is set beyond the bounds of the current text, it will be put back inside.

name: getWidth
desc: returns the width of the textbox depending on if background drawing is enabled

name: setCursorPositionEnd
desc: Moves the cursor to the very end of this text box.

name: setMaxStringLength
desc: Sets the maximum length for the text in this text box. If the current text is longer than this length, the current text will be trimmed.

name: setDisabledTextColour
desc: Sets the color to use for text in this text box when this text box is disabled.

name: setCanLoseFocus
desc: Sets whether this text box loses focus when something other than it is clicked.

name: getSelectedText
desc: returns the text between the cursor and selectionEnd

name: getMaxStringLength
desc: returns the maximum number of character that can be contained in this textbox

name: clearChatMessages
desc: Clears the chat.

name: printChatMessageWithOptionalDeletion
desc: prints the ChatComponent to Chat. If the ID is not 0, deletes an existing Chat Line of that ID from the GUI

name: getSentMessages
desc: Gets the list of messages previously sent through the chat GUI

name: addToSentMessages
desc: Adds this string to the list of sent messages, for recall using the up/down arrow keys

name: resetScroll
desc: Resets the chat scroll (executed when the GUI is closed, among others)

name: getChatOpen
desc: Returns true if the chat GUI is open

name: deleteChatLine
desc: finds and deletes a Chat line by ID

name: calcSaveDirName
desc: Determine a save-directory name from the world name

name: toggleMoreWorldOptions
desc: Toggles between initial world-creation display, and "more options" display.\nCalled when user clicks "More World Options..." or "Done" (same button, different labels depending on current display).

name: showMoreWorldOptions
desc: Shows additional world-creation options if toggle is true, otherwise shows main world-creation elements

name: recreateFromExistingWorld
desc: Set the initial values of a new world to create, from the values from an existing world.\n \nCalled after construction when a user selects the "Recreate" button.

name: updateDisplayState
desc: Sets displayed GUI elements according to the current settings state

name: setButtonDelay
desc: Sets the number of ticks to wait before enabling the buttons.

name: copyLinkToClipboard
desc: Copies the link to the system clipboard.

name: onLayersChanged
desc: Would update whether or not the edit and remove buttons are enabled, but is currently disabled and always disables the buttons (which are invisible anyways)

name: hasSelectedLayer
desc: Returns whether there is a valid layer selection

name: getSentHistory
desc: input is relative and is applied directly to the sentHistoryCursor so -1 is the previous message, 1 is the next message from the current cursor position

name: drawSprite
desc: Draws a sprite from assets/textures/gui/container/stats_icons.png

name: drawGuiContainerBackgroundLayer
desc: Draws the background layer of this container (behind the items).

name: drawSlot
desc: Draws the given slot: any item in it, the slot's background, the hovered highlight, etc.

name: drawGuiContainerForegroundLayer
desc: Draw the foreground layer for the GuiContainer (everything in front of the items)

name: drawItemStack
desc: Draws an ItemStack.\n \nThe z index is increased by 32 (and not decreased afterwards), and the item is then rendered at z=200.

name: drawActivePotionEffects
desc: Display the potion effects list

name: drawEntityOnScreen
desc: Draws an entity on the screen looking toward the cursor.

name: setCurrentCreativeTab
desc: Sets the current creative tab, restructuring the GUI as needed.

name: drawTab
desc: Draws the given tab and its background, deciding whether to highlight the tab or not based off of the selected index.

name: renderCreativeInventoryHoveringText
desc: Renders the creative inventory hovering text if mouse is over it. Returns true if did render or false otherwise. Params: current creative tab to be checked, current mouse x position, current mouse y position.

name: needsScrollBars
desc: returns (if you are not on the inventoryTab) and (the flag isn't set) and (you have more than 1 page of items)

name: getSelectedTabIndex
desc: Returns the index of the currently selected tab.

name: displayGuiScreen
desc:
Sets the argument GuiScreen as the main (topmost visible) screen.

WARNING: This method is not thread-safe. Opening GUIs from a thread other than the main thread may cause many different issues, including the GUI being rendered before it has initialized (leading to unusual crashes). If on a thread other than the main thread, use {@link #addScheduledTask}: 

minecraft.addScheduledTask(() -> minecraft.displayGuiScreen(gui));

name: middleClickMouse
desc: Called when user clicked he's mouse middle button (pick block)

name: rightClickMouse
desc: Called when user clicked he's mouse right button (place)

name: getDifficulty
desc: Get the server's difficulty

name: saveToFile
desc: Saves this CrashReport to the given file and returns a value indicating whether we were successful at doing so.

name: onDisconnect
desc: Invoked when disconnecting, the parameter is a ChatComponent describing the reason for termination

name: handleBlockChange
desc: Updates the block and metadata and generates a blockupdate (and notify the clients)

name: handleSpawnObject
desc: Spawns an instance of the objecttype indicated by the packet and sets its position and momentum

name: handleEntityStatus
desc: Invokes the entities' handleUpdateHealth method which is implemented in LivingBase (hurt/death), MinecartMobSpawner (spawn delay), FireworkRocket & MinecartTNT (explosion), IronGolem (throwing,...), Witch (spawn particles), Zombie (villager transformation), Animal (breeding mode particles), Horse (breeding/smoke particles), Sheep (...), Tameable (...), Villager (particles for breeding mode, angry and happy), Wolf (...)

name: handleSpawnPlayer
desc: Handles the creation of a nearby player entity, sets the position and held item

name: handleDestroyEntities
desc: Locally eliminates the entities. Invoked by the server when the items are in fact destroyed, or the player is no longer registered as required to monitor them. The latter  happens when distance between the player and item increases beyond a certain treshold (typically the viewing distance)

name: handleConfirmTransaction
desc: Verifies that the server and client are synchronized with respect to the inventory/container opened by the player and confirms if it is the case.

name: handleCustomPayload
desc: Handles packets that have room for a channel specification. Vanilla implemented channels are "MC|TrList" to acquire a MerchantRecipeList trades for a villager merchant, "MC|Brand" which sets the server brand? on the player instance and finally "MC|RPack" which the server uses to communicate the identifier of the default server resourcepack for the client to load.

name: handleWindowItems
desc: Handles the placement of a specified ItemStack in a specified container/inventory slot

name: handleEntityVelocity
desc: Sets the velocity of the specified entity to the specified value

name: handleWindowProperty
desc: Sets the progressbar of the opened window to the specified value

name: handleTeams
desc: Updates a team managed by the scoreboard: Create/Remove the team registration, Register/Remove the player-team-memberships, Set team displayname/prefix/suffix and/or whether friendly fire is enabled

name: handleUpdateScore
desc: Either updates the score with a specified value or removes the score for an objective

name: handleChat
desc: Prints a chatmessage in the chat GUI

name: handleDisconnect
desc: Closes the network channel

name: handleDisplayObjective
desc: Removes or sets the ScoreObjective to be displayed at a particular scoreboard position (list, sidebar, below name)

name: handleHeldItemChange
desc: Updates which hotbar slot of the player is currently selected

name: handleEntityMovement
desc: Updates the specified entity's position by the specified relative moment and absolute rotation. Note that subclassing of the packet allows for the specification of a subset of this data (e.g. only rel. position, abs. rotation or both).

name: handleBlockAction
desc: Triggers Block.onBlockEventReceived, which is implemented in BlockPistonBase for extension/retraction, BlockNote for setting the instrument (including audiovisual feedback) and in BlockContainer to set the number of players accessing a (Ender)Chest

name: handleChunkData
desc: Updates the specified chunk with the supplied data, marks it for re-rendering and lighting recalculation

name: handleMaps
desc: Updates the worlds MapStorage with the specified MapData for the specified map-identifier and invokes a MapItemRenderer for it

name: handleSetSlot
desc: Handles pickin up an ItemStack or dropping one in your inventory or an open (non-creative) container

name: handleEntityHeadLook
desc: Updates the direction in which the specified entity is looking, normally this head rotation is independent of the rotation of the entity itself

name: handleSignEditorOpen
desc: Creates a sign in the specified location if it didn't exist and opens the GUI to edit its text

name: handleUpdateTileEntity
desc: Updates the NBTTagCompound metadata of instances of the following entitytypes: Mob spawners, command blocks, beacons, skulls, flowerpot

name: handleEntityTeleport
desc: Updates an entity's position and rotation as specified by the packet

name: handleCloseWindow
desc: Resets the ItemStack held in hand and closes the window that is opened

name: handleAnimation
desc: Renders a specified animation: Waking up a player, a living entity swinging its currently held item, being hurt or receiving a critical hit by normal or magical means

name: handleSpawnMob
desc: Spawns the mob entity at the specified location, with the specified rotation, momentum and type. Updates the entities Datawatchers with the entity metadata specified in the packet

name: handleJoinGame
desc: Registers some server properties (gametype,hardcore-mode,terraintype,difficulty,player limit), creates a new WorldClient and sets the player initial dimension

name: handleExplosion
desc: Initiates a new explosion (sound, particles, drop spawn) for the affected blocks indicated by the packet.

name: handleEntityMetadata
desc: Invoked when the server registers new proximate objects in your watchlist or when objects in your watchlist have changed -> Registers any changes locally

name: handleSpawnExperienceOrb
desc: Spawns an experience orb and sets its value (amount of XP)

name: handleMultiBlockChange
desc: Received from the servers PlayerManager if between 1 and 64 blocks in a chunk are changed. If only one block requires an update, the server sends S23PacketBlockChange and if 64 or more blocks are changed, the server sends S21PacketChunkData

name: handleSpawnPainting
desc: Handles the spawning of a painting object

name: handleParticles
desc: Spawns a specified number of particles at the specified location with a randomized displacement according to specified bounds

name: handleEntityProperties
desc: Updates en entity's attributes and their respective modifiers, which are used for speed bonusses (player sprinting, animals fleeing, baby speed), weapon/tool attackDamage, hostiles followRange randomization, zombie maxHealth and knockback resistance as well as reinforcement spawning chance.

name: handleScoreboardObjective
desc: May create a scoreboard objective, remove an objective from the scoreboard or update an objectives' displayname

name: handleSpawnGlobalEntity
desc: Handles globally visible entities. Used in vanilla for lightning bolts

name: handleStatistics
desc: Updates the players statistics or achievements

name: handleBlockBreakAnim
desc: Updates all registered IWorldAccess instances with destroyBlockInWorldPartially

name: cleanup
desc: Clears the WorldClient instance associated with this NetHandlerPlayClient

name: getNetworkManager
desc: Returns this the NetworkManager instance registered with this NetworkHandlerPlayClient

name: processEnchantItem
desc: Enchants the item identified by the packet given some convoluted conditions (matching window, which should/shouldn't be in use?)

name: processConfirmTransaction
desc: Received in response to the server requesting to confirm that the client-side open container matches the servers' after a mismatched container-slot manipulation. It will unlock the player's ability to manipulate the container contents

name: processUseEntity
desc: Processes left and right clicks on entities

name: processClientStatus
desc: Processes the client status updates: respawn attempt from player, opening statistics or achievements, or acquiring 'open inventory' achievement

name: processCreativeInventoryAction
desc: Update the server with an ItemStack in a slot.

name: processPlayerDigging
desc: Processes the player initiating/stopping digging on a particular spot, as well as a player dropping items

name: processTryUseItem
desc: Called when a client is using an item while not pointing at a block, but simply using an item

name: processPlayer
desc: Processes clients perspective on player positioning and/or orientation

name: processPlayerAbilities
desc: Processes a player starting/stopping flying

name: processCustomPayload
desc: Synchronizes serverside and clientside book contents and signing

name: processClickWindow
desc: Executes a container/inventory slot manipulation as indicated by the packet. Sends the serverside result if they didn't match the indicated result and prevents further manipulation by the player until he confirms that it has the same open container/inventory

name: processClientSettings
desc: Updates serverside copy of client settings: language, render distance, chat visibility, chat colours, difficulty, and whether to show the cape

name: processKeepAlive
desc: Updates a players' ping statistics

name: processChatMessage
desc: Process chat messages (broadcast back to clients) and commands (executes)

name: processHeldItemChange
desc: Updates which quickbar slot is selected

name: processCloseWindow
desc: Processes the client closing windows (container)

name: processEntityAction
desc: Processes a range of action-types: sneaking, sprinting, waking from sleep, opening the inventory or setting jump height of the horse the player is riding

name: processInput
desc: Processes player movement input. Includes walking, strafing, jumping, sneaking; excludes riding and toggling flying/sprinting

name: handleSlashCommand
desc: Handle commands that start with a /

name: processHandshake
desc: There are two recognized intentions for initiating a handshake: logging in and acquiring server status. The NetworkManager's protocol will be reconfigured according to the specified intention, although a login-intention must pass a versioncheck or receive a disconnect otherwise

name: getBase64EncodedIconData
desc: Returns the base-64 encoded representation of the server's icon, or null if not available

name: setThunderStrength
desc: Sets the strength of the thunder.

name: renderMob
desc: Render the mob inside the mob spawner.

name: render
desc: Render this TileEntity at a given set of coordinates

name: markBlockRangeForRenderUpdate
desc: On the client, re-renders all blocks in this range, inclusive. On the server, does nothing.

name: bidiReorder
desc: Apply Unicode Bidirectional Algorithm to string and return a new possibly reordered string for visual rendering.

name: playDelayed
desc: Plays the sound in n ticks

name: play
desc: Play a sound

name: getAoBrightness
desc: Get ambient occlusion brightness

name: renderLivingLabel
desc: Renders an entity's name above its head

name: getLoadedShaders
desc: gets a map of loaded shaders for the ShaderType.

name: stringToBlendFunction
desc: Converts a blend function name to an id, returning add (32774) if not recognized.

name: updateMapTexture
desc: Updates a map {@link net.minecraft.client.gui.MapItemRenderer.Instance#mapTexture texture}

name: render
desc: Renders map and players to it

name: updateMapTexture
desc: Updates a map texture

name: getMapRendererInstance
desc: Returns {@link net.minecraft.client.gui.MapItemRenderer.Instance MapItemRenderer.Instance} with given map data

name: clearLoadedMaps
desc: Clears the currently loaded maps and removes their corresponding textures

name: saveScreenshot
desc: Saves a screenshot in the game directory with the given file name (or null to generate a time-stamped name).\nReturns an ITextComponent indicating the success/failure of the saving.

name: saveScreenshot
desc: Saves a screenshot in the game directory with a time-stamped filename.\nReturns an ITextComponent indicating the success/failure of the saving.

name: scrollTo
desc: Updates the gui slots ItemStack's based on scroll position.

name: generateNewRandomName
desc: Randomly generates a new name built up of 3 or 4 randomly selected words.

name: reseedRandomGenerator
desc: Resets the underlying random number generator using a given seed.

name: sendMessage
desc: Sends the given string to every player as chat message.

name: sendToAllNearExcept
desc: params: srcPlayer,x,y,z,r,dimension. The packet is not sent to the srcPlayer, but all other players within the search radius

name: createPlayerForUser
desc: also checks for multiple logins across servers

name: playDelayed
desc: Adds a sound to play in n tick

name: resume
desc: Resumes playing all currently playing sounds (after pauseAllSounds)

name: load
desc: Tries to add the paulscode library and the relevant codecs. If it fails, the master volume  will be set to zero.

name: pause
desc: Pauses all currently playing sounds

name: unload
desc: Cleans up the Sound System

name: stopAllSounds
desc: Stops all currently playing sounds

name: getMaxDelay
desc: Returns the maximum delay between playing music of this type.

name: getMinDelay
desc: Returns the minimum delay between playing music of this type.

name: keySet
desc: Gets all the keys recognized by this registry.

name: getId
desc: Gets the integer ID we use to identify the given object.

name: processPacket
desc: Passes this Packet on to the NetHandler for processing.

name: readPacketData
desc: Reads the raw packet data from the data stream.

name: writePacketData
desc: Writes the raw packet data to the data stream.

name: getData2
desc: pitch data for noteblocks

name: getData1
desc: instrument data for noteblocks

name: isSystem
desc: This method returns true if the type is SYSTEM or ABOVE_HOTBAR, and false if CHAT

name: getXCoordinate
desc: Gets the x coordinate to spawn the particle.

name: getXOffset
desc: Gets the x coordinate offset for the particle. The particle may use the offset for particle spread.

name: getParticleCount
desc: Gets the amount of particles to spawn

name: getZOffset
desc: Gets the z coordinate offset for the particle. The particle may use the offset for particle spread.

name: getYOffset
desc: Gets the y coordinate offset for the particle. The particle may use the offset for particle spread.

name: getZCoordinate
desc: Gets the z coordinate to spawn the particle.

name: getYCoordinate
desc: Gets the y coordinate to spawn the particle.

name: getParticleSpeed
desc: Gets the speed of the particle animation (used in client side rendering).

name: getExplosionResistance
desc: Returns how much this block can resist explosions from the passed in entity.

name: getRenderType
desc: The type of render function called. MODEL for mixed tesr and static model, MODELBLOCK_ANIMATED for TESR-only, LIQUID for vanilla liquids, INVISIBLE to skip all rendering\n@deprecated call via {@link IBlockState#getRenderType()} whenever possible. Implementing/overriding is fine.

name: ticksRandomly
desc: Returns whether or not this block is of a type that needs random ticking. Called for ref-counting purposes by ExtendedBlockStorage in order to broadly cull a chunk from the random chunk update list for efficiency's sake.

name: getPushReaction

Sets a block state into this world.Flags are as follows:
1 will cause a block update.
2 will send the change to clients.
4 will prevent the block from being re-rendered.
8 will force any re-renders to run on the main thread instead
16 will prevent neighbor reactions (e.g. fences connecting, observers pulsing).
32 will prevent neighbor reactions from spawning drops.
64 will signify the block is being moved.
Flags can be OR-ed

name: grow
desc:
Creates a new {@link AxisAlignedBB} that is expanded by the given value in all directions. Equivalent to {@link #grow(double, double, double)} with the given value for all 3 params. Negative values will shrink the AABB.
Side lengths will be increased by 2 times the value of the parameter, since both min and max are changed.
If contracting and the amount to contract by is larger than the length of a side, then the side will wrap (still creating a valid AABB - see samples on {@link #grow(double, double, double)}). @return A modified AABB.

name: shrink
desc:
Creates a new {@link AxisAlignedBB} that is expanded by the given value in all directions. Equivalent to {@link #grow(double)} with value set to the negative of the value provided here. Passing a negative value to this method values will grow the AABB.
Side lengths will be decreased by 2 times the value of the parameter, since both min and max are changed.
If contracting and the amount to contract by is larger than the length of a side, then the side will wrap (still creating a valid AABB - see samples on {@link #grow(double, double, double)}). @return A modified AABB.

name: contract
desc:
Creates a new {@link AxisAlignedBB} that has been contracted by the given amount, with positive changes decreasing max values and negative changes increasing min values.
If the amount to contract by is larger than the length of a side, then the side will wrap (still creating a valid AABB - see last sample).

Samples:

InputResult
new AxisAlignedBB(0, 0, 0, 4, 4, 4).contract(2, 2, 2)
box[0.0, 0.0, 0.0 -> 2.0, 2.0, 2.0]
new AxisAlignedBB(0, 0, 0, 4, 4, 4).contract(-2, -2, -2)
box[2.0, 2.0, 2.0 -> 4.0, 4.0, 4.0]
new AxisAlignedBB(5, 5, 5, 7, 7, 7).contract(0, 1, -1)
box[5.0, 5.0, 6.0 -> 7.0, 6.0, 7.0]
new AxisAlignedBB(-2, -2, -2, 2, 2, 2).contract(4, -4, 0)
box[-8.0, 2.0, -2.0 -> -2.0, 8.0, 2.0]

See Also:

  • {@link #expand(double, double, double)} - like this, except for expanding.
  • {@link #grow(double, double, double)} and {@link #grow(double)} - expands in all directions.
  • {@link #shrink(double)} - contracts in all directions (like {@link #grow(double)})
@return A new modified bounding box.

name: grow
desc:
Creates a new {@link AxisAlignedBB} that has been contracted by the given amount in both directions. Negative values will shrink the AABB instead of expanding it.
Side lengths will be increased by 2 times the value of the parameters, since both min and max are changed.
If contracting and the amount to contract by is larger than the length of a side, then the side will wrap (still creating a valid AABB - see last ample).

Samples:

InputResult
new AxisAlignedBB(0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1).grow(2, 2, 2)
box[-2.0, -2.0, -2.0 -> 3.0, 3.0, 3.0]
new AxisAlignedBB(0, 0, 0, 6, 6, 6).grow(-2, -2, -2)
box[2.0, 2.0, 2.0 -> 4.0, 4.0, 4.0]
new AxisAlignedBB(5, 5, 5, 7, 7, 7).grow(0, 1, -1)
box[5.0, 4.0, 6.0 -> 7.0, 8.0, 6.0]
new AxisAlignedBB(1, 1, 1, 3, 3, 3).grow(-4, -2, -3)
box[-1.0, 1.0, 0.0 -> 5.0, 3.0, 4.0]

See Also:

  • {@link #expand(double, double, double)} - expands in only one direction.
  • {@link #contract(double, double, double)} - contracts in only one direction.
    • {@link #grow(double)} - version of this that expands in all directions from one parameter.
  • {@link #shrink(double)} - contracts in all directions
@return A modified bounding box.

name: offset
desc: Offsets the current bounding box by the specified amount.

name: contains
desc: Returns if the supplied Vec3D is completely inside the bounding box

name: getAverageEdgeLength
desc: Returns the average length of the edges of the bounding box.

name: expand
desc:
Creates a new {@link AxisAlignedBB} that has been expanded by the given amount, with positive changes increasing max values and negative changes decreasing min values.

Samples:

InputResult
new AxisAlignedBB(0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1).expand(2, 2, 2)
box[0, 0, 0 -> 3, 3, 3]
 
new AxisAlignedBB(0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1).expand(-2, -2, -2)
box[-2, -2, -2 -> 1, 1, 1]
 
new AxisAlignedBB(5, 5, 5, 7, 7, 7).expand(0, 1, -1)
box[5, 5, 4, 7, 8, 7]

See Also:

  • {@link #contract(double, double, double)} - like this, except for shrinking.
  • {@link #grow(double, double, double)} and {@link #grow(double)} - expands in all directions.
  • {@link #shrink(double)} - contracts in all directions (like {@link #grow(double)})
@return A modified bounding box that will always be equal or greater in volume to this bounding box.

name: trimStringToWidth
desc:
Trims a string to a specified width, optionally starting from the end and working backwards.

Samples:

(Assuming that {@link #getCharWidth(char)} returns 6 for all of the characters in 0123456789 on the current resource pack)
InputReturns
trimStringToWidth("0123456789", 1, false)""
trimStringToWidth("0123456789", 6, false)"0"
trimStringToWidth("0123456789", 29, false)"0123"
trimStringToWidth("0123456789", 30, false)"01234"
trimStringToWidth("0123456789", 9001, false)"0123456789"
trimStringToWidth("0123456789", 1, true)""
trimStringToWidth("0123456789", 6, true)"9"
trimStringToWidth("0123456789", 29, true)"6789"
trimStringToWidth("0123456789", 30, true)"56789"
trimStringToWidth("0123456789", 9001, true)"0123456789"
